subSubSection.paragraph:
Aedeagus (
paratype
)

(
Fig. 8
). Basal piece longer than wide, laterally parallel-sided, dorsally open, apically rounded; remaining parts elongate, constricted laterally at base of parameres, apically lobed; median lobe elongate and narrow, apically rounded, narrowly bifid, shorter than parameres; parameres curved, elongate, with a triangular lateral tooth near base.
